    {
      "id": "xzIMpeh_OP3kxD8Qytn6p",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1810.027807792148,
      "y": 638.6064154634751,
      "width": 951.1593017578125,
      "height": 775,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bBJ",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1874179680,
      "version": 987,
      "versionNonce": 621496224,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1771740576597,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "DD2:\n- conflict resolution\n- retreiving edits\n\nsnapshotting -> send whole documents each time it updates (new versions every single edit)\nlast write wins -> only accept the one with the latest time stamp => data loss\noperational transform -> what we will use\nCRDT -> conflict free replication data types\n\n* opereational transform happens on both client & server side\n- server side needs to be done to have the source of truth\n- client side is so that \"earlier\" transaction can mutate the current change by another client\n- rely on server source of truth!\n\n1. client sends edits to WS server\n2. WS server broadcasts edits to every other client\n3. new client comes in & take new doc\n4. new client cant see edits\n\nhow to resolve?\n5. WS s erver needs to write updates to NoSQL DB\n6. WS service/ Document service can be the one merging current edits with retrieved documents\n*so even if dco storage is stale, edits can still be applied\n\nwhen should edits be uploaded to obj storage?\nwhen no one working on the doc\n7. makes sense since no one else is working on it\n8. send a job to the message q, queue the jobs to compact the edits from the DB\n9. compact service also delete the edits from the DB once done\n9. after compacting, make updates to object storage, where the CDN cache can also be validated\n",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "DD2:\n- conflict resolution\n- retreiving edits\n\nsnapshotting -> send whole documents each time it updates (new versions every single edit)\nlast write wins -> only accept the one with the latest time stamp => data loss\noperational transform -> what we will use\nCRDT -> conflict free replication data types\n\n* opereational transform happens on both client & server side\n- server side needs to be done to have the source of truth\n- client side is so that \"earlier\" transaction can mutate the current change by another client\n- rely on server source of truth!\n\n1. client sends edits to WS server\n2. WS server broadcasts edits to every other client\n3. new client comes in & take new doc\n4. new client cant see edits\n\nhow to resolve?\n5. WS s erver needs to write updates to NoSQL DB\n6. WS service/ Document service can be the one merging current edits with retrieved documents\n*so even if dco storage is stale, edits can still be applied\n\nwhen should edits be uploaded to obj storage?\nwhen no one working on the doc\n7. makes sense since no one else is working on it\n8. send a job to the message q, queue the jobs to compact the edits from the DB\n9. compact service also delete the edits from the DB once done\n9. after compacting, make updates to object storage, where the CDN cache can also be validated\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
